<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,1527,1806]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,305,1527,1553]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[311,369,1527,1553]" name="India" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">India</collectingCountry>
(Bengal, Kurseong) (
<bibRefCitation author="Kieffer, J. J." box="[609,800,1527,1554]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="59 - 66" refId="ref45659" refString="Kieffer, J. J. (1904) Description de quelques Cynipides exotiques dont l'un forme un genre nouveau. Bulletin de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de Metz, 2 (11), 59 - 66." type="journal article" year="1904">Kieffer 1904: 62</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dalla-Torre, K. W. von &amp; Kieffer, J. J." box="[811,1179,1527,1554]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="ref43265" refString="Dalla-Torre, K. W. von &amp; Kieffer, J. J. (1910) Cynipidae. Das Tierreich, 24. Friedlander &amp; Sohn, Berlin, 891 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 1077" type="book" year="1910">Dalla-Torre &amp; Kieffer 1910: 327</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mani, M. S." box="[1191,1315,1527,1554]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="ref46881" refString="Mani, M. S. (2000) Plant galls of India. Science Publishers Inc., Enfield, New Hampshire, 400 pp." type="book" year="2000">Mani 2000</bibRefCitation>
, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Penzes, Z. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Stone, G. N. &amp; Nicholls, J. A. &amp; Schweger, S. &amp; Bozso, M. &amp; Melika, G." box="[180,444,1563,1590]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="245 - 289" refId="ref49925" refString="Penzes, Z., Tang, C. - T., Stone, G. N., Nicholls, J. A., Schweger, S., Bozso, M. &amp; Melika, G. (2018) Current status of the oak gallwasp (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini) fauna of the Eastern Palaearctic and Oriental Regions. Zootaxa, 4433 (2), 245 - 289. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4433.2.2" type="journal article" year="2018">
Pénzes 
<emphasis box="[265,314,1563,1589]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al</emphasis>
. 2018: 276
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,1527,1806]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1600,1626]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1904" box="[321,513,1599,1625]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Neuroterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haasi">
<emphasis box="[321,513,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Neuroterus haasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith" authorityName="Smith" box="[856,1045,1599,1626]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spicata">
<emphasis box="[856,970,1600,1626]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Q. spicata</emphasis>
Smith
</taxonomicName>
, which has been synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Blume) Hatus. ex Soepadmo (Govaerts &amp; Frodin 1998)" authorityName="Hatus. ex Soepadmo (Govaerts &amp; Frodin" authorityYear="1998" baseAuthorityName="Blume" box="[151,1010,1635,1662]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Lithocarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis box="[151,378,1635,1661]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Lithocarpus elegans</emphasis>
(Blume) Hatus. ex Soepadmo (
<bibRefCitation author="Govaerts, R. &amp; Frodin, D. G." box="[725,1001,1635,1662]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="ref44205" refString="Govaerts, R. &amp; Frodin, D. G. (1998) World checklist and bibliography of Fagales (Betulaceae, Corylaceae, Fagaceae and Ticodendraceae). Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, 456 pp." type="book" year="1998">Govaerts &amp; Frodin 1998</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This is a very strange host association for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1840" box="[191,316,1672,1697]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Neuroterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[191,316,1672,1697]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Neuroterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In fact, 
<bibRefCitation author="Penzes, Z. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Stone, G. N. &amp; Nicholls, J. A. &amp; Schweger, S. &amp; Bozso, M. &amp; Melika, G." box="[416,638,1671,1698]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="245 - 289" refId="ref49925" refString="Penzes, Z., Tang, C. - T., Stone, G. N., Nicholls, J. A., Schweger, S., Bozso, M. &amp; Melika, G. (2018) Current status of the oak gallwasp (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini) fauna of the Eastern Palaearctic and Oriental Regions. Zootaxa, 4433 (2), 245 - 289. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4433.2.2" type="journal article" year="2018">
Pénzes 
<emphasis box="[500,549,1671,1697]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
suspect that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1904" box="[783,876,1671,1697]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Neuroterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haasi">
<emphasis box="[783,876,1671,1697]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">N. haasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Giraud" authorityYear="1859" box="[1004,1144,1672,1697]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Dryocosmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1004,1144,1672,1697]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Dryocosmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but whether it belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Giraud" authorityYear="1859" box="[151,291,1708,1733]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Dryocosmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,291,1708,1733]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Dryocosmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1840" box="[328,453,1708,1733]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Neuroterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[328,453,1708,1733]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Neuroterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be examined in further detail, including analysis of DNA sequence data.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,1527,1806]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1743,1769]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Biology.</emphasis>
Only the asexual generation has been described, which induces galls in young shoots of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hatus. ex Soepadmo (Govaerts &amp; Frodin" authorityYear="1998" baseAuthorityName="Blume" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Lithocarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Lithocarpus elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Table 1; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kieffer, J. J." box="[351,497,1779,1806]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="59 - 66" refId="ref45659" refString="Kieffer, J. J. (1904) Description de quelques Cynipides exotiques dont l'un forme un genre nouveau. Bulletin de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de Metz, 2 (11), 59 - 66." type="journal article" year="1904">Kieffer 1904</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dalla-Torre, K. W. von &amp; Kieffer, J. J." box="[509,822,1779,1806]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="ref43265" refString="Dalla-Torre, K. W. von &amp; Kieffer, J. J. (1910) Cynipidae. Das Tierreich, 24. Friedlander &amp; Sohn, Berlin, 891 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 1077" type="book" year="1910">Dalla-Torre &amp; Kieffer 1910</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
